<!-- ##### SECTION Title ##### -->
GeglBlend

<!-- ##### SECTION Short_Description ##### -->
Abstract class that represents common blend modes.

<!-- ##### SECTION Long_Description ##### -->
<para>
This is the abstract class that represents GeglImageOps with two image data
inputs, A, and B, combined in common blend modes. This class has a
<literal>opacity</literal> property which is used as multiplier that can be
applied to the second input (B).
</para>

<para>
Blend modes are described by the following formula for the case of 
premultiplied images (A,aA), (B,aB), with result (C,aC).
</para>

<literallayout>
C = (1-aB)*A + (1-aA)*B + aA*aB* Blend(A/aA, B/aB)
alphaC = aA + aB - aA*aB
</literallayout>

<para>
Different blend modes define the function Blend differently. 
For example Multiply defines Blend(x,y) = x*y.
</para>

